review 2: Beautiful and peaceful place. Very close to Penataran Temple, Lahangan sweet. Market place and black beaches. Employees are so nice, helpful and here to make your stay a dream! Thank to ‚ÄúYuman‚Äù who is take care to all my needs! 100% recommend
review 3: If you like off-the-beaten tracks and the countryside you'll love this place. The kitchen is simple but very tasty. The rooms are very clean and the garden is a gem of itself. Will be back again!
review 4: This is an absolutely beautiful place. The pictures do not do it justice. Impeccably kept gardens with full attention to detail. Delightful 1960's style gardens and swimming pool. Very peaceful. And to top it off the food was well priced and extremely delicious. The service also came in at 10/10 It was such a wonderful surprise to  find such perfect service and a care for details not normally found in Bali. I would recommend this to anyone.  However please note, this is NOT for TV lovers as there are none. Open the window shutters and enjoy the natural beauty of nature ...flow.
review 5:
Summary: amazing!
Stayed here for a week, with my bike! Amazing place with staff and management who are really helpful. The accommodations are just amazing, far above what I expected. Breakfast, lunch and dinner are fresh made and the swimming pool is without bleach!

review 1: Best value for money. We got all basic amenities with clean and spacious rooms. The place is not big but very well maintained and decorated. The breakfast in the morning is not much, but quite alright in this budget which came complimentary with stay. Owner Kalem was super helpful, helped us got great car and driver. She was always replying my questions in WhatsApp. Me and my family had great stay. Thank you very much!
